### 4.4 — Intelligence Synthesis Engine + Tax Compliance Engine → Regulatory Monitoring

> **Bottleneck Solved:** Regulatory Intelligence & Compliance
> **Live Demo:** [kusmus.org/solutions → Tax Compliance Engine](https://kusmus.org/solutions) *(same RAG architecture)*

We have already proven this architecture works. Our **Tax Compliance Engine** — live and testable at [kusmus.org](https://kusmus.org) — is fine-tuned on the complete Nigeria Tax Act 2025 and delivers 100% statutory accuracy with legal citation on every output. The same RAG pipeline, powered by a model that outscores GPT-5.1 on legal reasoning benchmarks, can be re-targeted at NITDA's regulatory corpus.

**Application for NITDA:**
- **Continuous Compliance Scanning:** The Intelligence Synthesis Engine continuously monitors the public digital footprints of registered tech companies, social media platforms, and IT service providers for compliance indicators.
- **Automated Compliance Reports:** Instead of quarterly manual audits, the system generates real-time compliance scorecards for each regulated entity.
- **Legal Citation Engine:** Every finding is backed by specific citations from the NITDA Act, Nigeria Data Protection Act, and Code of Practice for Online Platforms — using the same proven legal-RAG architecture deployed in our Tax Engine.
- **Enforcement Prioritization:** AI-ranked severity matrix enables NITDA to focus enforcement resources on the highest-risk non-compliant entities first.

| Before | After |
|---|---|
| Periodic manual audits | Continuous AI-powered monitoring |
| Weeks to produce compliance reports | Real-time compliance scorecards |
| No legal citation in reports | Every finding backed by statutory citation |

