### 4.5 — VLA Robotics → Physical Infrastructure Security

> **Bottleneck Solved:** Physical Security of National IT Assets

**VLA Robotics** interfaces with hardware vision systems — cameras and drones — to detect physical tampering, unauthorized access, and hardware anomalies in real-time.

**Application for NITDA:**
- **Data Center Surveillance:** AI-powered visual anomaly detection for NITDA-supervised data centers and critical IT infrastructure.
- **Autonomous Inspection:** Dispatch of visual inspection drones to alert coordinates at data farms, fiber landing stations, and government server rooms.
- **Hardware Diagnostics:** Monitors for physical signs of equipment degradation (overheating, unauthorized cable changes, tampering indicators).

| Before | After |
|---|---|
| Manual CCTV monitoring | AI-powered 24/7 visual anomaly detection |
| Human security patrols | Autonomous drone inspection |
| Post-incident investigation | Real-time tamper detection |

