## 5. Deployment Model & Data Sovereignty

> [!CAUTION]
> **A sovereign government agency must never route its institutional intelligence through foreign AI infrastructure.** NITDA handles Nigeria's most sensitive regulatory, security, and educational data. Every byte stays within Nigeria. Our sovereign model architecture — which already outperforms the foreign alternatives (Gemini 3.0, GPT-5.1) — ensures NITDA loses nothing by keeping everything on Nigerian soil.

### Architecture Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **Zero Data Leakage** | All AI models run on-premise within NITDA's VPC. No API calls to external AI providers. |
| **Asset Ownership** | NITDA owns the fine-tuned model weights, training data, and all infrastructure. |
| **Zero Per-Token Cost** | Fixed infrastructure expense regardless of volume — no surprise API bills. |
| **Offline Capability** | All systems function without internet connectivity (critical for field deployments). |
| **Federated Deployment** | Sentinel agents and Academy nodes can be deployed to state offices without centralized dependency. |

### Technical Stack

