## 6. Financial Model

### Infrastructure Cost Breakdown

> [!NOTE]
> A sovereign deployment means NITDA invests in **owning** its AI infrastructure — not renting foreign APIs. The upfront capital expenditure is higher, but eliminates recurring per-token costs, data exposure, and foreign dependency. All estimates below are based on current Nigerian market pricing as of Q1 2026.

#### 6.1 — GPU Compute Infrastructure (One-Time Capital Expenditure)

| Item | Specification | Qty | Unit Cost (₦) | Total (₦) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **NVIDIA A100 80GB SXM4** | Primary inference & fine-tuning GPU | 4 | ₦39,640,000 | ₦158,560,000 |
| **NVIDIA H100 80GB PCIe** | High-throughput training & heavy workloads | 2 | ₦60,620,000 | ₦121,240,000 |
| **GPU Server Chassis** | Supermicro/Dell PowerEdge (dual Xeon, 512GB RAM, NVMe) | 2 | ₦15,000,000 | ₦30,000,000 |
| **Network Switching (25GbE)** | High-speed internal fabric for multi-GPU | 1 | ₦5,000,000 | ₦5,000,000 |
| **UPS & Power Conditioning** | Online double-conversion UPS (20kVA) | 2 | ₦8,000,000 | ₦16,000,000 |
| **Storage Array (NVMe)** | 100TB enterprise NVMe for model weights & datasets | 1 | ₦12,000,000 | ₦12,000,000 |
| | | | **GPU CAPEX Subtotal** | **₦342,800,000** |

