### Phased Engagement Model

Rather than deploying the full ₦550M in one tranche, we recommend a phased approach:

| Phase | Duration | Solutions Deployed | Estimated Investment (₦) |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Phase 1: Pilot** | 3 months | Intelligence Synthesis + Sentinel (2x A100, Starlink, engineering) | ₦120,000,000 – ₦150,000,000 |
| **Phase 2: Scale** | 6 months | + Autodidactic Academy (additional GPUs, hub rollout) | ₦180,000,000 – ₦220,000,000 |
| **Phase 3: Full Stack** | 12 months | + Compliance Engine + VLA Robotics (full infrastructure) | ₦200,000,000 – ₦250,000,000 |

### Cost-Benefit Analysis

| Cost Driver | Without AI (Status Quo) | With Kusmus AI (Sovereign) |
|---|---|---|
| Failed IT Projects (56% failure rate) | **Billions** annually in wasted expenditure | AI risk scores reduce failure rate to <20% |
| CERRT 24/7 Staffing | ₦500M+ annual salaries + overhead | Sentinel: autonomous 24/7 coverage, ₦0 additional staffing |
| 3MTT Instructor Scale (3M learners) | Physically impossible at current budget | 1:1 AI tutor at fixed infrastructure cost |
| Compliance Monitoring | Large team, quarterly manual reports | Continuous real-time monitoring, zero lag |
| **Foreign API Dependency** | **₦200M-₦500M/year** in token costs to OpenAI/Google | **₦0** — sovereign model, zero per-token cost |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The sovereign model eliminates the single largest hidden cost of AI adoption: **per-token API fees**. At NITDA's projected query volume across 5 systems, foreign API costs would exceed ₦200M-₦500M annually — more than the entire recurring cost of sovereign infrastructure.


